# Easy Pretzel Bites
## Ingredients
- 2 cups all-purpose flour
- 1 cup plain Greek yogurt
- 1 tablespoon baking powder
- 1/4 cup baking soda (for the bath)
- Coarse sea salt (for sprinkling)

## Method
1. Preheat your oven to 425F
2. Combine floud and baking powder and mix in the greek yogurt. Mix until well combined (Over mixing will lead to tough bites).
3. Lightly flour the work surcace and turn the dough out. Roll it into a log and cut into bite-sized pieces.
4. In a large pot, bring 4 cups of water to a boil and add the baking soda. Once boiling, reduce to a simmer
5. Drop a few bites into he water at a time (don't overcrowd). Boil each batch for about 30 seconds. use a slotted spoon to remove and place them on a lined baking sheet to dry.
6. Sprinkle coarse sea salt on top of each bite and bank in the oven for 12-15 minutes (or until golden brown).
7. Let cool and enjoy